%I A397060 #11 Jun 18 2026 22:14:43
%S A397060 720,1800,2961,7632
%N A397060 Integers x such that there exist four integers 0<y<=z<=t<=w such that sigma(x)^2*psi(x)*phi(x)^2 = x^5 + y^5 + z^5 + t^5 + w^5.
%C A397060 The numbers x, y, z, t and w form a sigma^2*psi*phi^2-quintic quintuple.
%H A397060 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-2-psi-phi-2-quintic-quintuples/blob/main/A397060">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A397060 (720, 232, 280, 560, 656) is such a quintuple because sigma(720)^2 * psi(720) * phi(720)^2 = 2418^2 * 1728 * 192^2 = 720^5 + 232^5 + 280^5 + 560^5 + 656^5.
%o A397060 (Python) # See Links.
